<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,690,1507]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1267,1291]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Etymology.</emphasis>
From Latin, 
<taxonomicName box="[495,542,1268,1291]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Artchawakomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pius">
<emphasis box="[495,542,1268,1291]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">pius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(= holy, pious), referring to the general appearance as if it were wearing a ceremonial dress in pious Buddhists’ country; an adjective.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
